    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-06-02T11:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-06-02T11:00:00-05:00" n="53"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d53">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/5171d</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Russia</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_FDR1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Francis</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-06-02T11:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1917, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1460. Most urgent. Department’s 1426, May 22, noon,<note n="1" xml:id="d53fn1"
                        >See footnote 1, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_86">p.
                            86</ref>.</note> and 1456, May 31, 6 p.m., concerning presidential
                    communication. Immediate answer imperative. Report date and hour of receipt of
                    No. 1426.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
